		Real-Time Interview Answer

		Functional Interface is an interface that contains only one 
		abstract method. It is mainly used to implement lambda expressions in Java. 
		We can use @FunctionalInterface annotation to ensure the interface has only 
		one abstract method. Example: Runnable, Comparator, Predicate etc.
		
